NEW YORK. MY. Henry
B. King president, United States
Brewers Association announced
the appointment of William A.
Sawyer, of Phoenix, as state
representative and legal repre-
sentative for Arizona. Sawyer,
who has been the USBA Legal
Representative since 1859, as
sumes the former position, re-
placing Morley E. Fox, who has
resigned.


The USBA, which has had rep
resentation in Arizona since 1910
is a national trade association Of
the brewing industry. Its purpose
is to promote broader public
understanding of the industry S
place in American life and bus
mess. Sawyer will continue to
maintain contacts with state and
local public officials, law en-
forcement authorities and the
press, as we'll as with brewers,
beer wholesalers and retailers.

USBA NAMES SAWYER
AS STATE REPRESENTATIVE
